The Stack class will have three methods: push, pop, and peek. The push method will add elements to the stack, the pop method will remove the top element from the stack, and the peek method will return the top element without removing it.

Here's the implementation:

class Stack {
    constructor() {
        this.items = [];
    }

    push(item) {
        this.items.push(item);
    }

    pop() {
        if (this.isEmpty()) {
            throw new Error("Stack is empty");
        }
        return this.items.pop();
    }

    peek() {
        if (this.isEmpty()) {
            throw new Error("Stack is empty");
        }
        return this.items[this.items.length - 1];
    }

    isEmpty() {
        return this.items.length === 0;
    }
}

